@mtlsBase = https://localhost:10443

# Edit ~/.config/httptui/config.json:
# {
#   "certificates": {
#     "localhost": {
#       "cert": "./certs/client.crt",
#       "key": "./certs/client.key",
#       "ca": "./certs/ca.crt"
#     }
#   }
# }

##### Quick test of HTTPS endpoint (client cert is not required)

### quick ping (no cert is required)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/ping


##### Test for no client certificate
##### Expect: /optional -> client_certificate=null, /verify -> 403

### No Cert - /optional (Expect: returns success, cert is null)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/optional

### No Cert - /verify (Expect: 403)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/verify

### No Cert - /echo-cert (Expect: 400)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/echo-cert


##### Test for client certificate
##### Prerequisites: httptui config is ready with "localhost" certificates

### With Cert - /echo-cert (returns client certificate details)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/echo-cert

### With Cert - /optional (returns client certificate details)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/optional

### With Cert - /verify (returns cert details + TLS version/cipher suite)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/verify

### With Cert - /headers (echoes request headers + certificate info)
GET {{mtlsBase}}/mtls/headers
Accept: application/json
X-Custom-Header: mtls-test
